# Courtify agent practices

Full context lives in `AGENTS.md` (start with **Agent quick start**). Do not re-invent patterns already implemented there.

## UI/UX (F1-app style)

- **Layouts:** `Courtify/Shared/CourtifyLayout.swift` only — `CourtifyFullBleedScreen` (Home), `CourtifyHeroScrollScreen` (Schedule/Rankings), `CourtifyPlainScrollScreen` (Widgets).
- **Safe-area traps (fixed — do not reintroduce):**
  1. Never `.ignoresSafeArea(edges: .top)` on a view wrapping a `GeometryReader` (safeTop becomes 0).
  2. Never offset hero background up inside a `ScrollView` (clips → dark band under status bar). ScrollView gets `.ignoresSafeArea(edges: .top)`; pad hero *content* with safeTop.
  3. Never put paywall behind `OnboardingFlowView`’s top `safeAreaInset` chrome — solid band over the live marquee (blackout). Paywall owns full-bleed backdrop + close (`managesOwnCloseButton`).
- **Chrome:** `midnightGreen` base, gradient heroes, `opticYellow` highlights, `courtGreen` tile subtitles, `CourtifyTileDivider` hairlines. `ProfileIconButton` + `.settingsSheet` on **all four tabs**.
- **Motion:** `CourtifyMotion` + `.courtifyButton(...)` only (soft `sensoryFeedback` on press-down). Root uses `.courtifyInteractiveChrome()`; selection uses `.courtifySelectionFeedback`. No new haptics/animation curves.
- Use `WidgetTheme.contentInset` (16pt) for all small/medium copy — do not invent per-widget padding. Home widgets use `WidgetTheme.contentInsets` (adds stamp clearance at the bottom). Atmospheric `WidgetAtmosphere` / `WidgetTextureOverlay` (aurora default; carbon/mesh/spotlight/velvet optional) beat flat single-color fills; skip muddy tournament logos as backgrounds. Overlay chrome must stay inside the preview-sized ZStack (never `maxWidth: .infinity` overlays that stretch a lone small card). Keep hero cutouts and stats in separate columns on medium cards. Lock Screen gallery previews get a thin white F1-style stroke. Unlocked card tap → `WidgetShareView` (`.courtifyButton(.card)` haptic) with Share → system share sheet; locked → paywall. Share asset includes **Made by Courtify on App Store** stamp (`MadeByCourtifyAppStoreStamp`). **Widget stamp:** `WidgetMadeByStamp` via `.courtifyWidgetCanvas()` — opticYellow, not grey; keep clear of bottom copy via `contentInsets`.
- **Made by Courtify stamp:** every home-screen widget must use `.courtifyWidgetCanvas()` so `WidgetMadeByStamp` appears (default bottom-trailing; `.bottomCenter` / `.bottomLeading` when corners are crowded). Lock Screen kinds: `stamp: .none` only.
- **Widget colors (Premium):** `WidgetColorStyle` + `WidgetColorPickerSheet` for `favorite` / `favorite-medium` / standings / `live` / `order`. Includes named presets (Clay/Grass/…) plus a **Custom** `ColorPicker` swatch, plus **Texture** (Aurora default). Free users tapping the gallery color control open the paywall (never the sheet). Tournament widgets (`next-*`, `countdown`, `calendar`) keep brand/surface colors — no recolor UI. Gradient slider persists on finger-up only (no per-tick timeline reload). Sheet defaults to `.large`; gradient + texture sit above the preset grid.
- **Custom player photos:** `PlayerTorsoPhotoView` / `TennisPlayerPhotoView` + monochrome `PlayerSilhouetteView` — never letter placeholders, never a gradient/fill wash behind torso silhouettes.
- **Settings favorite cards:** equal-width `FavoriteCard`s (`minWidth: 0`); artwork overlay-only; Change padded above corner radius. Slam art via `FavoriteSlamLogoBadge`. Quota miss → silhouette + helper text.
- **Paywall / splash backdrop:** `CourtifyMarqueeBackground` — live SwiftUI widget cards (not `marquee-widget-strip`, not player photos). Avoid positive marquee `startOffset` gutters (left blackout strip).
- **WidgetKit:** register every gallery card via `CourtifyWidgetCatalog` + nested `OtherBundle().body` when exceeding 10 kinds (do not pass a `WidgetBundle` type as a `Widget`). Lock Screen kinds live in `LockScreenWidgets.swift`.
- **Slam logos (pickers):** `AssetCatalogImage` — not `CachedBundledImage` (stale in-memory cache).

## API cost (strict)

**Upstream plan:** RapidAPI Matchstat **Pro ($29/mo)** on Tennis API - ATP WTA ITF. Basic (50 req/day) is **not** viable for custom photos / season W/L. Do not migrate vendors without an explicit product decision.

| Data | Source | When it fetches |
|------|--------|-----------------|
| Favorite player hero (bundled) | `player-*-hero` assets | Never at runtime |
| Custom favorite rank/photo | `/api/player-lookup` + `/api/player-photo` | **On pick only**; Worker KV 30d + Cloudflare edge photo cache 30d |
| Custom favorite season W/L | `/api/player-season-record` → `PlayerSeasonRecordCache` | **On pick only**; Worker KV 24h |
| Tournament schedule | `TournamentCalendar` | Never |
| Rankings / live / order of play | Worker via `WidgetDataStore` | Pull-to-refresh only |
| Onboarding top-10 player row | Worker | **Once ever** via `refreshOnceForOnboarding()` |

On appear: `loadCachedPayload()` only (always reload from app-group disk). No `refresh()` without user pull or the one-time onboarding exception.

**Onboarding picks:** Tour / favorite player / Grand Slam write to app-group keys as the user continues each step. Home is gated on `hasCompletedOnboarding` only — never skip onboarding solely because RevenueCat Pro or referral bypass flipped mid-flow (drops unsaved favorites).

**Quota:** Do not expand widget-data to top 100. Do not fetch season W/L inside shared refresh. Lookup = one rankings call per uncached name, no 429 retries. Photos go through Worker edge cache. On 429/503 refresh, show alert and keep cached rankings. Custom photo failure → helper UX, not a blank broken hero. Worker skips RapidAPI when remaining quota is below reserve (5 on Basic-sized limits, 100 on Pro+).

Worker: on-demand KV refresh (max every 6 h), **5** upstream calls (live + ATP/WTA rankings + ATP/WTA fixtures), ATP/WTA top 20 (`pageSize=20`). Deploy: `npx wrangler deploy` when quota allows (prefer after Pro upgrade).

## Simulator testing (no tap automation)

- Simulator: iPhone 17 Pro `744F6ACA-F0CC-4105-8794-D798EF7726CC`
- **Default dev loop:** `bash scripts/dev-sim-hot-reload.sh` (UI + backend). Avoid Xcode Canvas — large asset catalog causes "empty catalog import…" and high CPU. See `AGENTS.md` → **Local dev modes**.
- **After asset or cache changes:** `simctl uninstall … com.courtify.xyz` before reinstall.
- Build: `xcodebuild … -derivedDataPath .derivedData` → `simctl install` → `simctl launch`
- Launch args: `-UITestHome`, `-UITestTab schedule|rankings|widgets`, `-UITestSettings`, `-UITestWidgetFilter`, `-UITestWidgetOnly <id>`, `-UITestPaywall`
- Wait ~7s after launch before screenshots.
- Seed rankings: write `widgetDataPayloadCache` hex to app-group plist.
- When verifying insets from screenshots, measure at 3× (iPhone 17 Pro); anti-aliased card edges can under-count padding by ~6px.

## Release

- Bump `CURRENT_PROJECT_VERSION` in `Courtify.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj` before TestFlight
- Upload: `bash scripts/upload-testflight.sh` (uses `scripts/xcode-env.sh` → Xcode 26.0.1)
- Commit/push when the user asks; deploy Worker after `index.js` changes
